sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant Client as External Client
    participant GW as API Gateway<br/>(Kuadrant/Authorino)
    participant API as API Server<br/>8000/TCP
    participant PG as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP
    participant Redis as Redis/Valkey<br/>6379/TCP
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP
    participant Proc as Processor<br/>9090/TCP
    participant LLM as llm-d Endpoint<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    participant GC as Garbage Collector<br/>9091/TCP

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 1: Batch Job Submission

    Client->>GW: POST /v1/files<br/>Auth: API Key / SA Token
    GW->>GW: Validate credentials<br/>(Kuadrant/Authorino)
    GW->>API: Forward authenticated request<br/>X-MaaS-Username: {tenant}
    API->>S3: Upload input file<br/>HTTPS/443, AWS IAM credentials
    S3-->>API: Upload confirmation
    API->>PG: Store file metadata<br/>pgx/5432, TLS 1.2+
    PG-->>API: file_id
    API-->>GW: 200 OK {file_id}
    GW-->>Client: File uploaded

    Client->>GW: POST /v1/batches<br/>{input_file_id, model, endpoint}
    GW->>API: Forward authenticated request
    API->>PG: Create batch record<br/>pgx/5432, TLS 1.2+
    PG-->>API: batch_id
    API->>Redis: Enqueue job (sorted set)<br/>RESP/6379, score=SLO deadline
    Redis-->>API: Enqueued
    API-->>GW: 200 OK {batch_id, status: validating}
    GW-->>Client: Batch created

    Note over Proc,LLM: Flow 2: Batch Job Processing

    loop Poll every 5s
        Proc->>Redis: ZPOPMIN (dequeue highest priority)<br/>RESP/6379
        Redis-->>Proc: Job payload
    end

    Proc->>PG: Fetch job metadata<br/>pgx/5432, TLS 1.2+
    PG-->>Proc: Batch record + file refs
    Proc->>S3: Download input file<br/>HTTPS/443, AWS IAM
    S3-->>Proc: JSONL content

    Proc->>Proc: Preprocess → Execution Plans<br/>(per-model request grouping)

    Proc->>PG: Update status: in_progress<br/>CAS update
    PG-->>Proc: Confirmed

    loop For each request (AIMD concurrency)
        Proc->>LLM: POST inference request<br/>Bearer token, optional TLS/mTLS
        alt Success (2xx)
            LLM-->>Proc: Inference result
            Proc->>Proc: AIMD: additive increase
        else Rate limited (429) or Error (5xx)
            LLM-->>Proc: Error response
            Proc->>Proc: AIMD: multiplicative decrease<br/>(backoff_factor: 0.5)
            Proc->>Proc: Exponential backoff retry
        end
    end

    Proc->>S3: Upload output file<br/>HTTPS/443, AWS IAM
    S3-->>Proc: Upload confirmation
    Proc->>PG: Store output file metadata
    PG-->>Proc: output_file_id
    Proc->>PG: Update status: completed<br/>CAS update
    PG-->>Proc: Confirmed

    Note over GC,S3: Flow 3: Garbage Collection

    loop Every 30m (collector)
        GC->>PG: Query expired batches & files<br/>pgx/5432, TLS 1.2+
        PG-->>GC: Expired items list
        GC->>S3: Delete expired file blobs<br/>HTTPS/443, AWS IAM
        S3-->>GC: Deleted
        GC->>PG: Delete expired metadata<br/>(max_concurrency: 10)
        PG-->>GC: Cleaned
    end

    loop Every 60m (reconciler)
        GC->>PG: Query non-terminal jobs
        PG-->>GC: Candidate orphans
        GC->>Redis: Check queue & in-flight<br/>RESP/6379
        Redis-->>GC: Status data
        alt Job orphaned, SLO still valid
            GC->>Redis: Re-enqueue job
        else Job orphaned, SLO expired
            GC->>PG: CAS update → expired/failed
        end
    end
